0", "url": "https://dblp.uni-trier.de/rec/journals/corr/abs-2309-16650"}, {"type": "pdf", "link": "https://export.arxiv.org/pdf/2309.16650"}, {"type": "semantic_scholar.abstract", "link": "174a3290ff0040e0f6a7a0b43bcd752c456350a0", "url": "https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/174a3290ff0040e0f6a7a0b43bcd752c456350a0"}, {"type": "corpusid", "link": "263134620"}], "flags": [{"name": "validation", "value": 1}], "validated": true, "citation_count": 0, "excerpt": null},{"paper_id": "bcdfe8a0a1c7305f0dfa5e442e60b7ca", "title": "Rethinking Teacher-Student Curriculum Learning through the Cooperative Mechanics of Experience", "abstract": "Teacher-Student Curriculum Learning (TSCL) is a curriculum learning framework that draws inspiration from human cultural transmission and learning. It involves a teacher algorithm shaping the learning process of a learner algorithm by exposing it to controlled experiences. Despite its success, understanding the conditions under which TSCL is effective remains challenging. In this paper, we propose a data-centric perspective to analyze the underlying mechanics of the teacher-student interactions in TSCL. We leverage cooperative game theory to describe how the composition of the set of experiences presented by the teacher to the learner, as well as their order, influences the performance of the curriculum that is found by TSCL approaches. To do so, we demonstrate that for every TSCL problem, there exists an equivalent cooperative game, and several key components of the TSCL framework can be reinterpreted using game-theoretic principles. Through experiments covering supervised learning, reinforcement learning, and classical games, we estimate the cooperative values of experiences and use value-proportional curriculum mechanisms to construct curricula, even in cases where TSCL struggles. The framework and experimental setup we present in this work represent a novel foundation for a deeper exploration of TSCL, shedding light on its underlying mechanisms and providing insights into its broader applicability in machine learning.", "authors": [{"author": {"author_id": "c56654ca191f0174d58cb9a5f1442f15", "name": "Manfred Diaz", "links": [{"type": "openreview", "link": "~Manfred_Diaz1"}, {"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "38994607"}, {"type": "xplore", "link": "37086310742"}]}, "affiliations": [{"institution_id": "0fcc67870b4775549451cc5c4061ec7e", "name": "Mila, University of Montreal", "category": "unknown"}, {"institution_id": "28e9e3e07d018dc25de1f00cbc5087eb", "name": "University of Montreal", "category": "unknown"}, {"institution_id": "78a83265183550c66a78ff9b5f9b960f", "name": "Mila", "category": "unknown"}]}, {"author": {"author_id": "f7755e3792a26b14d79e8804ff7c530f", "name": "Liam Paull", "links": [{"type": "!semantic_scholar", "link": "147812093"}, {"type": "bio", "link": "liam-paull"}, {"type": "email.mila", "link": "paulll@mila.quebec"}, {"type": "mag", "link": "2198295625"}, {"type": "mag", "link": "2873594279"}, {"type": "openreview", "link": "~Liam_Paull1"}, {"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "2265536920"}, {"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "2276201926"}, {"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "2294873530"}, {"type": "semantic_scholar", "link": "3198259"}, {"type": "wpid_en", "link": "27832"}, {"type": "wpid_fr", "link": "27835"}, {"type": "xplore", "link": "37087071649"}, {"type": "xplore", "link": "37935956000"}]}, "affiliations": [{"institution_id": "0a4595cdfa4e6d9d22cc74f6a6a2666f", "name": "Canada CIFAR AI Chair", "category": "unknown"}, {"institution_id": "0fcc67870b4775549451cc5c4061ec7e", "name": "Mila, University of Montreal", "category": "unknown"}, {"institution_id": "28e9e3e07d018dc25de1f00cbc5087eb", "name": "University of Montreal", "category": "unknown"}, {"institution_id": "78a83265183550c66a78ff9b5f9b960f", "name": "Mila", "category": "unknown"}]}, {"author": {"author_id": "8531479bf415fa6d2a50d851af0b5ab9", "name": "Andrea Tacchetti", "links": [{"type": "openreview", "l